(15, 'Computing Science Instructional Labs Hardware', '<div class="parsys main_content">\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h2><a name="top"></a>Overview</h2>\n<p>The Computing Science Instructional Labs (CSIL) currently have the following hardware setup in multiple campuses and study areas. Please <a href="http://www.sfu.ca/computing/about/support/how-to-contact-helpdesk.html">report issues to <strong>helpdesk</strong></a> if you need further assistance.</p>\n<hr /></div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h2>Latest updates:</h2>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h2>Burnaby Campus</h2>\n<p>CSIL@Burnay is located in the Applied Science Building (ASB), and consists of the following <u>Study Areas</u>:</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p>In<strong> ASB9700</strong>, we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>31 Dell Optpliex 9020 Workstations<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: dualboot&nbsp;<em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Intel Quad Core i7-4790 w/HD Graphics 4600 (Haswell GT2)</li>\n<li>RAM: 16GB (1600MHz DDR3)</li>\n<li>Display: 27" LCDs, 2560x1440@32bit color, on DisplayPort with mDP cable</li>\n<li>Network interface: Intel 825xx Gigabit Ethernet Controller</li>\n<li>No DVD drives</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p>In <strong>ASB9804</strong>, we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>31 Dell OptiPlex 7010 Workstations\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System:&nbsp;dualboot&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Intel Quad Core i7 3770 w/HD Graphics 4000 (Ivy Bridge)</li>\n<li>RAM: 16GB (1600MHz DDR3)</li>\n<li>Display: 27" LCDs, 2560x1440@32bit color (41p), on Dual-Link DVI port with DisplayPort-DVI adapter</li>\n<li>Network interface: Intel 82579LM (Lewisville) Gigabit Ethernet Controller</li>\n<li>DVD Writers installed on all computers</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>&nbsp;1 MIDI keyboard (installed upon request to HelpDesk)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p>In&nbsp;<strong>ASB9838 North</strong>, we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>71 Dell OptiPlex 9020 Workstations\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System:&nbsp;dualboot <em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>Intel Quad Core i7-4790 CPU w/HD Graphics 4600 (Haswell GT2)</li>\n<li>RAM: 32GB (1600MHz DDR3)</li>\n<li>Display: 27" LCDs, 2560x1440@32bit color, on DisplayPort</li>\n<li>Network interface: Intel I217-M (ClarkvilleLM) Network Adapter</li>\n<li>DVD Writers installed on all computers</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\n<li>1 network printer (HP LaserJet 8100) on ITS print release system</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p><strong>In ASB9820,</strong> we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>15 OptiPlex 9020 Workstations\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System:&nbsp;&nbsp;dualboot <em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Intel Quad Core i7 3770 w/HD Graphics 4600 (Haswell GT2)</li>\n<li>RAM: 16GB (1600MHz DDR3)</li>\n<li>Display: 27" LCDs, 2560x1440@32bit color</li>\n<li>Network interface: Intel Gigabit Ethernet Controller</li>\n<li>No DVD drives</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p><strong>In each team room ASB9812, ASB9814,</strong> we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2 OptiPlex 7010/9020 Workstations\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System:&nbsp;&nbsp;dualboot <em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Intel Quad Core i7</li>\n<li>GPU: Intel HD Graphics</li>\n<li>Display: 27" LCDs, 2560x1440@32bit color</li>\n<li>Network interface: Intel Gigabit Ethernet Controller</li>\n<li>No DVD drives</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p><strong>In ASB9840,</strong> we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>38 OptiPlex 7040 Workstations\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System:&nbsp;&nbsp;dualboot <em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Intel Quad Core i7-6700 w/HD Graphics 530 (Skylake)</li>\n<li>RAM: 32GB (1600MHz DDR3)</li>\n<li>discrete GPU: ASB9840-A02 to A08, ASB9840-B## systems each has 1 <a href="https://www.zotac.com/us/product/graphics_card/zotac-geforce-gtx-1050-ti-mini#spec" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ZOTAC NVIDIA Geforce GTX 1050 Ti</a> installed</li>\n<li>Display: 27" LCDs, 2560x1440@32bit color</li>\n<li>Network interface: Intel Gigabit Ethernet Controller I219-LM</li>\n<li>No DVD drives</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p><strong>In ASB9700 and team room ASB9816,</strong> we have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>10 Apple Mac Pro Workstations\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Managed Mac (OS X)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h3>About special GPUs in the lab</h3>\n<p>We have installed 15 new video cards (NVidia Geforce GTX 1050 Ti, from ZOTAC) in ASB 9840. The computers equiped with these cards are: asb9840-a02 to a08 and asb9840-b##. These cards have the <a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-zone" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CUDA</a> Compute Capability of 6.1. The CUDA development tools are configured under Ubuntu on these systems.</p>\n<p>There are 9 descrete video cards (NVidia Geforce GT 720, MSI N720-2GD3LP) in ASB 9838 North-East side. The computers equiped with these cards are: asb9838n-a12 to a16 and asb9838n-b13 to b16. These cards have the&nbsp;<a href="https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-zone">CUDA</a>&nbsp;Compute Capability of 3.5. The CUDA development tools (incl. Caffe) are configured under Ubuntu on these systems. (Please note: to utilize the projector in the area, computer asb9838n-a12 is now located at the west side of the hallway.)</p>\n<p>People taking paralle computing or graphics related courses have priority to use these systems.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h3>About Projectors in the lab</h3>\n<p>There is a mounted projector for each study area; each is accompanied by a remote, a motorized screen and a special VGA cable. You may locate the projector''s VGA connector near these workstations:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>asb9700-a05</li>\n<li>asb9804-a05</li>\n<li>asb9838n-a07 (displays to two projectors)</li>\n<li>asb9820-a01</li>\n<li>asb9840-a05</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Please remember, after your presentation is finished:</p>\n<p style="margin-left: 40px;"><strong>Turn off the projector</strong> to save the lamp and electricity.<br /> Put the screen back to the top.<br /> Make sure the switch (for screen motors) is on "off" (not up, not down).<br /> detach the VGA cable from the computer.</p>\n<p>Click <a href="http://www.sfu.ca/computing/about/support/data-projectors.html">here</a> for more details on how to use the projectors.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h3>About powerbars in the lab</h3>\n<p>The powerbars are provided for personal computing devices only. Plugging in any other devices is prohibited.</p>\n<p>Please <strong>do not unplug any device already plugged</strong> into the powerbar - others may be using the device.</p>\n<p>Please remember to unplug &amp; bag your own device before you leave.</p>\n<p><u>Safety warning: trip hazard</u> -&nbsp; you may only use the powerbar on the same row you sit on; otherwise, the cables may cause people stumble.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h3>About DisplayPort cables and mini DisplayPort cables in the lab</h3>\n<p>All DisplayPort cables and mini DisplayPort cables are for the School''s equipment use only.</p>\n<p><strong>Warning</strong>: <u>disconnecting any DisplayPort cable or mini DisplayPort cable from the CSIL workstations for personal use is <strong>prohibited</strong></u>.</p>\n<p>The <u>CSIL access will be revoked</u> if you use any of these cables for your personal device.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h3>About extra VGA cables in the lab</h3>\n<p>The extra VGA cables are provided for people to hook up our LCD panels to their personal laptops.</p>\n<p>If you change the display settings of the monitor to use the extra VGA connection as the input source, please reset to proper one when you leave - this means you should see the login screen on the LCD panel.</p>\n<p><strong>Warning</strong>: <u>disconnecting any VGA cable from the CSIL workstations for personal use is <strong>prohibited</strong></u>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<h3>About the sound system</h3>\n<p>A sound system has been installed in ASB9838 North in 2013.</p>\n<p>You may book the microphone from ASB 9971.</p>\n<p>Since the sound system covers the whole area of ASB9838 North, an exclusive booking of the area is required.</p>\n<p>Please turn the amplifier volume knob to off position after using this system.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class=""><hr />\n<h2>Surrey Campus</h2>\n<p><strong>Windows Lab - Surrey 4050</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>30 Dell OptiPlex 9010 Workstations<br />\n<ul>\n<li>OS: dualboot&nbsp;<em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Core i7</li>\n<li>All with DVD writers</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Linux Lab - Surrey 4080</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>30 Dell OptiPlex 7040 Workstations<br />\n<ul>\n<li>OS: dualboot&nbsp;<em><a href="https://help.ubuntu.com/16.04/">Ubuntu 16.04 LTS Xenial Xerus</a></em> and Windows 7 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>CPU: Core i7</li>\n<li>All with CD writers</li>\n<li>1 network printer (HP LaserJet 2320dn) on ITS print release system</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class=""><hr />\n<h2>Special notes on programming</h2>\n<p>Operating System (O/S) level programming (e.g. with <strong>fork()</strong> calls) must be done on <strong>Linux workstations in CSIL</strong>. No other hosts should be used on SFU network, <u>no exceptions</u>.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class=""><hr />\n<h2>CSIL Linux Servers</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>punch.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 Virtual Server (File serving for notes, subversion)<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Ubuntu 12.04</li>\n<li>2 Core 2.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>(under maintenance, not in service) cs-nx.csil.sfu.ca: (1 Virtual Server : Linux Terminal Server)\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Ubuntu 12.04</li>\n<li>2 Core 2.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>(under construction) <strong>cs-cpu.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 Virtual Server (Linux CPU server)\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Ubuntu 14.04</li>\n<li>2 Core 2.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>csil-cpu[2-6].cs.surrey.sfu.ca</strong>: 5 Virtual Servers (Linux CPU server)\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Ubuntu 14.04</li>\n<li>2 Core 2.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n<li>Many thanks to Ben and Jason who have created and provide support for these servers.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href="CMPT-471-Networking-Frequently-Asked-Questions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cs-vnl.csil.sfu.ca</a></strong>: 1 Virtual Server (Remote Linux Terminal Server for cmpt471)<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Ubuntu 14.04</li>\n<li>2 Core 2.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>(not in service) <strong>gemini.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: CPU server for special courses</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class=""><hr />\n<h2><a href="CSIL-Windows-FAQ#windows-servers">CSIL Windows Servers</a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>leto.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 PowerEdge R710 Application server (Remote Desktop login)<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Windows Server 2008 R2 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>2 Quad Core Xeon X5560 CPU, 24GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>freesia.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 Virtual Server (File serving for profiles and notes)<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Windows Server 2008 Enterprise w/SP2</li>\n<li>2 Core 3.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>cypress.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 Virtual Server (SQL Server for database course)<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Windows Server 2008 R2 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>2 Core 3.0 GHz CPU, 4GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong><a href="CSIL-Windows-Course-Software" target="_blank" rel="noopener">cs-gaia.cmpt.sfu.ca</a></strong>: 1 Virtual Server (File serving for software packages)\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Windows Server 2012 R2 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>2 Core 3.0 GHz CPU, 6GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>(</strong><u>under construction, not in service</u><strong>) cs-heracles.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 Virtual Server (web server)\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Windows Server 2012 R2 Enterprise w/SP1</li>\n<li>4 Core 3.0 GHz CPU, 8GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>(<u>under construction, not in service</u>) <strong>cs-demeter.csil.sfu.ca</strong>: 1 Virtual Server (SQL Server for courses using databases)<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Operating System: Windows Server 2012 R2 Enterprise w/ SP1 (SQL Server 2014)</li>\n<li>2 Core 3.0 GHz CPU, 8GB RAM</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class="">\n<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="#top">top</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">\n<div class=""><hr />\n<h2>The updates history of CSIL</h2>\n<p>We have deployed total of 45 brand new Dell Optiplex 7040 workstations with new 27" LCDs in CSIL@Burnaby (2017.02.10)</p>\n<p>We also deployed total of 15 ZOTAC NVIDIA Geforce GTX 1050 Ti graphics cards (GPU) in room ASB 9840 in CSIL@Burnaby (2017.02.10)</p>\n<p>We have added mDP-VGA (Mini DisplayPort to VGA) adapters to all projector connections (2016.04.01)</p>\n<p>We have deployed total of 43 brand new Dell Optiplex 9020 workstations with 27" LCDs in CSIL@Burnaby (2015.12.04)</p>\n<p>We have put total of 43 brand new Dell Optiplex 9020 workstations with 27" LCDs in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2015.12.04)</p>\n<p>We have 9 NVidia GT720 video cards configured at ASB 9838North East. (2015.10.01)</p>\n<p>We have put total of 71 brand new Dell Optiplex 9020 workstations with 27" LCDs in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2015.03.26)</p>\n<p>We have put a new project in ASB9838 North East in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2014.11.06)</p>\n<p>We have put total of 40 brand new Dell Optiplex 7010 workstations with 27" LCDs in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2014.04.25)</p>\n<p>We have put a total of 38 Dell Optiplex 7010 workstations in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2013.12.16)</p>\n<p>We have installed a sound system in the study area of ASB9838 North in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2013.05.05)</p>\n<p>We have put a total of 21 powerbars for people''s personal computing devices in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2012.05.05)</p>\n<p>We have put extra VGA (video) cables to computers in many study areas in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2012.05.05)</p>\n<p>We have put a total of 102 Dell OptiPlex 790 workstations in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2012.05.04)</p>\n<p>We have put a total of 32 Dell Precision T3500 workstations in CSIL@Burnaby. (@2012.03.28)</p>\n<p>We have put a total of 134 24" LCDs in CSIL@Burnaby. All of the computers in CSIL@Burnaby are currently using 24" flat screen monitors. (@2012.03.02)</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="text parbase section">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>', '2017-07-16 12:58:09', 'Computing-Science-Instructional-Labs-Hardware'),
